events.description: Thailand's consumer price index data for January 2026 showed a 0.66% year-on-year decline, marking the tenth consecutive month of deflation.

facts.fact_text: Thailand consumer prices fell 0.66% year-on-year in January 2026.

evidences.evidence_text: Consumer prices in Thailand fell 0.66% year-on-year in January 2026

facts.fact_text: January 2026 marked the tenth consecutive month of deflation in Thailand.

evidences.evidence_text: This marked the tenth consecutive month of deflation

facts.fact_text: Core consumer prices in Thailand rose 0.60% annually in January.

evidences.evidence_text: core consumer prices, which exclude volatile items such as food and energy, continued to rise, up 0.60% annually

facts.fact_text: The Thai central bank's inflation target range is 1%–3%.

evidences.evidence_text: keeping inflation well below the central bank’s 1%–3% target range.

claims.claim_text: Headline consumer prices are expected to remain negative through April before turning positive.
claims.author: Commerce ministry

evidences.evidence_text: Headline consumer prices are expected to remain negative through April before turning positive.

claims.claim_text: The decline in consumer prices was driven by lower energy prices and government measures to ease living costs.
claims.author: Commerce ministry

evidences.evidence_text: The commerce ministry said the decline was driven by lower energy prices and government measures to ease living costs.
